Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle to sharpish turn. Rectangular stamp with caduceus and grape cluster symbols. Clay fine pink-buff; dull slip.
Curator's comments: Common stamp. Petrie drew several (EES Archive XVII). Name Midas.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1038)
